====Usage notes====
* ''Decline'', ''refuse'', ''forbear'', ''refrain'': ''Decline'' is gentler than ''[[refuse]]'' and carries a connotation that the non-acceptance is an acceptable or anticipated option (''decline an invitation'') or the result of a considered decision (''the judge declined to grant the motion''). ''Refuse'' has a stronger connotation of rejection, firmness, resistance, or non-compliance. For example, if someone ''declines'' to give their name, that suggests they were given a choice and elected not to give their name. If someone ''refuses'' to give their name, the connotation is more toward a suggestion that they normally should have given their name and are being intransigent. ''[[forbear|Forbear]]'' or ''[[refrain]]'', conversely, suggest choosing not to do something that one might indulge in or be tempted to do (''refrain from smoking''), with ''forbear'' having an added connotation of showing some fortitude in withstanding the temptation (''forbear to show anger''). ''Refrain'' can also be used to refer to a general policy or preference rather than a choice on a single occasion.


